   Background
   Our research program is focused on the analysis of the
   three-dimensional structures of macromolecular assemblies using high
   resolution electron microscopy. Members of our group work on different,
   yet, complementary aspects of structural analysis. These include
   electron crystallographic studies of two-dimensional protein crystals,
   "single particle" approaches to analyze the structures of protein
   complexes and determination of the structures of large subcellular
   assemblies using electron tomography.
   A significant fraction of our research effort is devoted to developing
   and implementing novel methods for specimen preparation, high
   throughput data acquisition and computational analysis.
